{"type":"message","id":"597c6703","parentId":"f6f316b2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:55:56.990Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_YbvCciC6QpP2FWYMjjw7wbjI|fc_037c94a0d844dc370169d1c12a8cdc8195be7bd898b95a6eb3","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/DIAGNOSTICS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/DIAGNOSTICS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":23712,"output":36,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23748,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775354149794,"responseId":"resp_037c94a0d844dc370169d1c1294fe88195902470e23afe407d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"02f59b03","parentId":"597c6703","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:55:57.044Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_YbvCciC6QpP2FWYMjjw7wbjI|fc_037c94a0d844dc370169d1c12a8cdc8195be7bd898b95a6eb3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# DIAGNOSTICS.md\n\nUse this pattern for status / health / readiness / \"is it normal\" questions.\nPrefer layered answers over vague judgments.\n\n## Core Answer Shape\n1. Installed / present\n2. Loaded / enabled\n3. Callable / reachable\n4. Functionally verified\n5. Dependency / permission / credential gaps\n6. Concrete next step\n\n## General Rules\n- Do not collapse uncertainty into confidence language.\n- \"Enabled\" is weaker than \"functionally verified\".\n- \"File exists\" is weaker than \"runtime dependency works\".\n- If a direct functional test is possible, prefer it over process-name guessing.\n- If environment access is blocked (permissions, Docker socket, browser not started), say so explicitly.\n- If you cannot verify a layer, mark it unknown instead of pretending it passed.\n\n## OpenClaw Core Service Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - `openclaw` CLI exists\n  - expected workspace/plugin paths exist\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - `openclaw status`\n  - plugin or capability appears as enabled\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - related tool call succeeds without immediate transport/config failure\n- Functionally verified:\n  - run a real, minimal capability test\n- Gaps:\n  - missing plugin, blocked daemon, missing config, missing permission\n- Next step:\n  - restart gateway, fix config, inspect logs, or run functional test\n\n## Memory / Plugin Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - plugin folder/file exists\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - appears in `openclaw status`\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - memory tool call succeeds\n- Functionally verified:\n  - store + recall roundtrip succeeds\n- Gaps:\n  - indexing delay, backend error, missing dependency, permission issue\n- Next step:\n  - re-test after delay, inspect logs, narrow to write vs recall path\n\n## Skills Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - skill directory exists\n  - `SKILL.md` exists and can be read\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - skill is discoverable/in injected list if applicable\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - required first-class tools can be invoked\n- Functionally verified:\n  - representative happy-path test succeeds\n- Gaps:\n  - missing binaries, missing API keys, missing browser/login state, bad path\n- Next step:\n  - separate skill file health from runtime dependency health\n\n## Browser Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - browser tool exists\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - browser subsystem reports available\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - `browser status` / `tabs` works\n- Functionally verified:\n  - start/open/snapshot succeeds on a simple page\n- Gaps:\n  - browser not running, cdp not ready, attach prompt not approved, profile mismatch\n- Next step:\n  - start browser, use correct profile, or ask user to approve attach\n\n## Feishu Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - Feishu tools available\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - app scopes are present\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - lightweight API call succeeds (e.g. scopes/info/read)\n- Functionally verified:\n  - actual doc/wiki/bitable read or write succeeds as needed\n- Gaps:\n  - missing scope, invalid token, wrong doc/chat id, permission denied\n- Next step:\n  - inspect scopes, confirm target identifier, retry smallest valid operation\n\n## Search / Web Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - `web_search` / `web_fetch` tool exists\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - tool callable by platform\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - request succeeds at transport/auth layer\n- Functionally verified:\n  - returns expected result body/snippets/content\n- Gaps:\n  - API key missing, remote site blocked, extraction failure, anti-bot\n- Next step:\n  - configure key, fall back to `web_fetch` or browser, use scrape-specific workflow\n\n## CTF Environment Check\n- Installed / present:\n  - skill exists\n  - expected binaries/packages are installed\n- Loaded / enabled:\n  - language/runtime available (python3, pip3, etc.)\n- Callable / reachable:\n  - binaries execute / Python imports succeed\n- Functionally verified:\n  - representative toolchain test works for target category\n- Gaps:\n  - missing gdb/pwntools/z3/sqlmap/ffuf/etc.\n- Next step:\n  - report by category (web/crypto/reverse/pwn), then provide install plan in tiers\n\n## Suggested Output Style\n- Conclusion: one line\n- Evidence:\n  - Installed:\n  - Loaded:\n  - Callable:\n  - Verified:\n  - Gaps:\n- Next step:\n\n## Tiny Example\n- Installed: skill file exists\n- Loaded: plugin appears in system status\n- Callable: tool invocation succeeds\n- Functionally verified: write + recall test succeeds\n- Gap: search API key missing\n- Next step: configure key or use alternate fetch path\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775354157041}}
