{"type":"message","id":"86efd57b","parentId":"ea2aaa3e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:55:02.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7Ig1SClpD1zTJ70oFdhkvxFr|fc_0ffb88811cc378450169d1dd159aa48190944110a3ad13dcc3","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/PLAN_MODE.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/PLAN_MODE.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":30019,"output":34,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30053,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775361299051,"responseId":"resp_0ffb88811cc378450169d1dd1491ec8190a21a9ee4dc3885ed"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f17e496","parentId":"86efd57b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:55:02.363Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7Ig1SClpD1zTJ70oFdhkvxFr|fc_0ffb88811cc378450169d1dd159aa48190944110a3ad13dcc3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PLAN_MODE.md\n\nUse plan mode for non-trivial tasks before doing meaningful execution.\n\n## When to Enter Plan Mode\n- Multi-step tasks with dependencies\n- Anything likely to touch multiple files or systems\n- Debugging where the cause is not yet clear\n- Risky or costly actions\n- Tasks with branching options or tradeoffs\n- Any request where \"just start doing stuff\" would create thrash\n\n## What a Good Plan Looks Like\nKeep it short but concrete.\n\n### Minimum structure\n- Goal\n- Constraints / risks\n- Steps\n- First action\n\n### Example\n- Goal: verify whether a plugin is really healthy\n- Constraints: Docker socket access may be blocked; process name may not exist\n- Steps:\n  1. Check status/load state\n  2. Run functional verification\n  3. Inspect gaps if verification fails\n- First action: run status and a small roundtrip test\n\n## Execution Rules\n- Planning is not stalling. Keep it concise.\n- After planning, move into execution unless the task clearly requires confirmation first.\n- If new evidence invalidates the plan, revise it instead of pretending the old plan still fits.\n- For long tasks, checkpoint after major steps.\n- Update `WORKSTATE.md` when the plan meaningfully changes or work is interrupted.\n\n## When Not to Use Plan Mode\n- Simple factual questions\n- Single low-risk reads/checks\n- Tiny one-file edits with obvious intent\n- Cases where planning would be longer than doing\n\n## Output Style\nFor most tasks, 3â6 bullets is enough.\nDo not write a giant roadmap unless the user asked for one.\n\n## Relationship to Other Files\n- Use `RISK_TIERS.md` to judge caution level\n- Use `DIAGNOSTICS.md` for health/status investigations\n- Use `CHECKPOINTS.md` for long-running work snapshots\n- Use `WORKSTATE.md` to preserve current active state\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775361302361}}
{"type":"message","id":"063b5e79","parentId":"6f17e496","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:55:06.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_wARnVSyrRhSbs8MAYXOZ5NAg|fc_0678939b8f1abd450169d1dd1973288193bad4d211d7ce0bc4","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/openclaw/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/openclaw/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":30461,"output":45,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30506,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775361302364,"responseId":"resp_0678939b8f1abd450169d1dd181d308193ae8b6d2fe26cb3d5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9125a65b","parentId":"063b5e79","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:55:06.372Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_wARnVSyrRhSbs8MAYXOZ5NAg|fc_0678939b8f1abd450169d1dd1973288193bad4d211d7ce0bc4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: clawhub\ndescription: Use the ClawHub CLI to search, install, update, and publish agent skills from clawhub.com. Use when you need to fetch new skills on the fly, sync installed skills to latest or a specific version, or publish new/updated skill folders with the npm-installed clawhub CLI.\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"clawhub\",\n              \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install ClawHub CLI (npm)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# ClawHub CLI\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g clawhub\n```\n\nAuth (publish)\n\n```bash\nclawhub login\nclawhub whoami\n```\n\nSearch\n\n```bash\nclawhub search \"postgres backups\"\n```\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nclawhub install my-skill\nclawhub install my-skill --version 1.2.3\n```\n\nUpdate (hash-based match + upgrade)\n\n```bash\nclawhub update my-skill\nclawhub update my-skill --version 1.2.3\nclawhub update --all\nclawhub update my-skill --force\nclawhub update --all --no-input --force\n```\n\nList\n\n```bash\nclawhub list\n```\n\nPublish\n\n```bash\nclawhub publish ./my-skill --slug my-skill --name \"My Skill\" --version 1.2.0 --changelog \"Fixes + docs\"\n```\n\nNotes\n\n- Default registry: https://clawhub.com (override with CLAWHUB_REGISTRY or --registry)\n- Default workdir: cwd (falls back to OpenClaw workspace); install dir: ./skills (override with --workdir / --dir / CLAWHUB_WORKDIR)\n- Update command hashes local files, resolves matching version, and upgrades to latest unless --version is set\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775361306369}}
