{"type":"message","id":"715f71b6","parentId":"a0d946a8","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:56:10.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"æć·Čç»æćź**èŁć°æŹæșæèœçźćœ**äșïŒäœ**OpenClaw èżæČĄèŻć«ć°ćź**ă  \nèżéćžžèŻŽæèżć·źäžæ­„ïŒ**æèœæ«æ/æćĄéćŻ**ïŒæèèżäžȘ skill ççźćœç»æ/ćæ°æźäžćźćšçŹŠććœćçæŹçćç°è§ćă\n\næććż«éçäžçŒæŹć°ć·Čæ skill çç»æïŒćŻčæŻäžèżäžȘćæŻäžæŻć°äșä»äčïŒććłćźèŠäžèŠç»§ç»­äżźă","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0083665ee16b82040169d1dd53fb6081939dce22238118b397\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ayXFWKEIcRq6bDIKfuBMgLzS|fc_0083665ee16b82040169d1dd55dab8819387131cf90b375110","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"set -e\nprintf '== compare local custom skills ==\\n'\nfor d in /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/feishu-bot-manager; do\n  echo \"\\n### $d\"\n  find \"$d\" -maxdepth 2 | sed 's#^#/##' | head -50\n  [ -f \"$d/package.json\" ] && echo '-- package.json --' && sed -n '1,120p' \"$d/package.json\"\n  [ -f \"$d/SKILL.md\" ] && echo '-- SKILL.md head --' && sed -n '1,40p' \"$d/SKILL.md\"\ndone","workdir":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"set -e\\nprintf '== compare local custom skills ==\\\\n'\\nfor d in /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/feishu-bot-manager; do\\n  echo \\\"\\\\n### $d\\\"\\n  find \\\"$d\\\" -maxdepth 2 | sed 's#^#/##' | head -50\\n  [ -f \\\"$d/package.json\\\" ] && echo '-- package.json --' && sed -n '1,120p' \\\"$d/package.json\\\"\\n  [ -f \\\"$d/SKILL.md\\\" ] && echo '-- SKILL.md head --' && sed -n '1,40p' \\\"$d/SKILL.md\\\"\\ndone\",\"workdir\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":37498,"output":365,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775361356041,"responseId":"resp_0083665ee16b82040169d1dd518f048193a359929470c9f6ce"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c72bf23","parentId":"715f71b6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:56:10.832Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ayXFWKEIcRq6bDIKfuBMgLzS|fc_0083665ee16b82040169d1dd55dab8819387131cf90b375110","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"== compare local custom skills ==\n\n### /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/references\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/references/codex-tools.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/references/gemini-tools.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/SKILL.md\n-- SKILL.md head --\n---\nname: using-superpowers\ndescription: Use when starting any conversation - establishes how to find and use skills, requiring Skill tool invocation before ANY response including clarifying questions\n---\n\n<SUBAGENT-STOP>\nIf you were dispatched as a subagent to execute a specific task, skip this skill.\n</SUBAGENT-STOP>\n\n<EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>\nIf you think there is even a 1% chance a skill might apply to what you are doing, you ABSOLUTELY MUST invoke the skill.\n\nIF A SKILL APPLIES TO YOUR TASK, YOU DO NOT HAVE A CHOICE. YOU MUST USE IT.\n\nThis is not negotiable. This is not optional. You cannot rationalize your way out of this.\n</EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>\n\n## Instruction Priority\n\nSuperpowers skills override default system prompt behavior, but **user instructions always take precedence**:\n\n1. **User's explicit instructions** (CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, direct requests) â highest priority\n2. **Superpowers skills** â override default system behavior where they conflict\n3. **Default system prompt** â lowest priority\n\nIf CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, or AGENTS.md says \"don't use TDD\" and a skill says \"always use TDD,\" follow the user's instructions. The user is in control.\n\n## How to Access Skills\n\n**In Claude Code:** Use the `Skill` tool. When you invoke a skill, its content is loaded and presented to youâfollow it directly. Never use the Read tool on skill files.\n\n**In Gemini CLI:** Skills activate via the `activate_skill` tool. Gemini loads skill metadata at session start and activates the full content on demand.\n\n**In other environments:** Check your platform's documentation for how skills are loaded.\n\n## Platform Adaptation\n\nSkills use Claude Code tool names. Non-CC platforms: see `references/codex-tools.md` (Codex) for tool equivalents. Gemini CLI users get the tool mapping loaded automatically via GEMINI.md.\n\n# Using Skills\n\n### /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill/SKILL.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/find-skills-skill/_meta.json\n-- SKILL.md head --\n---\nname: find-skills\ndescription: \"Search and discover OpenClaw skills from various sources. Use when: user wants to find available skills, search for specific functionality, or discover new skills to install.\"\nhomepage: https://clawhub.com\nmetadata: { \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"đ\", \"requires\": { \"bins\": [] } } }\n---\n\n# Find Skills Skill\n\nSearch and discover OpenClaw skills from various sources.\n\n## When to Use\n\nâ **USE this skill when:**\n\n- \"Find skills for [task]\"\n- \"Search for OpenClaw skills\"\n- \"What skills are available?\"\n- \"Discover new skills\"\n- \"Find skills by category\"\n\n## When NOT to Use\n\nâ **DON'T use this skill when:**\n\n- Installing skills â use `clawhub install`\n- Managing installed skills â use `openclaw skills list`\n- Creating new skills â use skill-creator skill\n\n## Sources for Finding Skills\n\n### 1. ClawHub (Primary)\n```bash\n# Search skills\nnpx clawhub search \"keyword\"\n\n# Browse categories\nnpx clawhub browse\n```\n\n\n### /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/boundaries.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/corrections.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/heartbeat-rules.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/HEARTBEAT.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/learning.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/memory-template.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/memory.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/openclaw-heartbeat.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/operations.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/reflections.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/scaling.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/setup.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/SKILL.md\n//vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/self-improving/_meta.json\n-- SKILL.md head --\n---\nname: Self-Improving + Proactive Agent\nslug: self-improving\nversion: 1.2.16\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/self-improving\ndescription: \"Self-reflection + Self-criticism + Self-learning + Self-organizing memory. Agent evaluates its own work, catches mistakes, and improves permanently. Use when (1) a command, tool, API, or operation fails; (2) the user corrects you or rejects your work; (3) you realize your knowledge is outdated or incorrect; (4) you discover a better approach; (5) the user explicitly installs or references the skill for the current task.\"\nchangelog: \"Clarifies the setup flow for proactive follow-through and safer installation behavior.\"\nmetadata: {\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"đ§ \",\"requires\":{\"bins\":[]},\"os\":[\"linux\",\"darwin\",\"win32\"],\"configPaths\":[\"~/self-improving/\"],\"configPaths.optional\":[\"./AGENTS.md\",\"./SOUL.md\",\"./HEARTBEAT.md\"]}}\n---\n\n## When to Use\n\nUser corrects you or points out mistakes. You complete significant work and want to evaluate the outcome. You notice something in your own output that could be better. Knowledge should compound over time without manual maintenance.\n\n## Architecture\n\nMemory lives in `~/self-improving/` with tiered structure. If `~/self-improving/` does not exist, run `setup.md`.\nWorkspace setup should add the standard self-improving steering to the workspace AGENTS, SOUL, and `HEARTBEAT.md` files, with recurring maintenance routed through `heartbeat-rules.md`.\n\n```\n~/self-improving/\nâââ memory.md          # HOT: â€100 lines, always loaded\nâââ index.md           # Topic index with line counts\nâââ heartbeat-state.md # Heartbeat state: last run, reviewed change, action notes\nâââ projects/          # Per-project learnings\nâââ domains/           # Domain-specific (code, writing, comms)\nâââ archive/           # COLD: decayed patterns\nâââ corrections.md     # Last 50 corrections log\n```\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| Topic | File |\n|-------|------|\n| Setup guide | `setup.md` |\n| Heartbeat state template | `heartbeat-state.md` |\n| Memory template | `memory-template.md` |\n| Workspace heartbeat snippet | `HEARTBEAT.md` |\n| Heartbeat rules | `heartbeat-rules.md` |\n| Learning mechanics | `learning.md` |\n\n### /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/skills/feishu-bot-manager\n//vol1/@