{"type":"message","id":"7901ab7b","parentId":"27f41545","timestamp":"2026-04-05T12:58:29.016Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"æćçĄźèź€ćœćææČĄæâćć»ș agentâçç°æćœä»€æçźćœçșŠćźïŒćç»äœ çŽæ„ćć»șïŒéżćæć·„é éç»æă","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04d4768b795231fd0169d25c6af73c819b94fea1f99f3e4074\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_50Z67d5GMSHvO3CeujZ3nMRs|fc_04d4768b795231fd0169d25c6fdfd8819b9015dfba488457da","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"OPENCLAW_BIN=/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/openclaw/node_modules/.bin/openclaw\n($OPENCLAW_BIN agents --help || true) && echo '---' && ($OPENCLAW_BIN agent --help || true) && echo '---AGENT DIRS---' && find /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents -maxdepth 3 -type f | sed -n '1,120p'","workdir":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"OPENCLAW_BIN=/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/openclaw/node_modules/.bin/openclaw\\n($OPENCLAW_BIN agents --help || true) && echo '---' && ($OPENCLAW_BIN agent --help || true) && echo '---AGENT DIRS---' && find /vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents -maxdepth 3 -type f | sed -n '1,120p'\",\"workdir\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":54260,"output":185,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775393888312,"responseId":"resp_04d4768b795231fd0169d25c6986f0819b84227c8e060da677"}}
{"type":"message","id":"64cb7895","parentId":"7901ab7b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T12:58:36.700Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_50Z67d5GMSHvO3CeujZ3nMRs|fc_04d4768b795231fd0169d25c6fdfd8819b9015dfba488457da","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"đŠ OpenClaw 2026.4.2 (d74a122) â You had me at 'openclaw gateway start.'\n\nUsage: openclaw agents [options] [command]\n\nManage isolated agents (workspaces + auth + routing)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add a new isolated agent\n  bind          Add routing bindings for an agent\n  bindings      List routing bindings\n  delete        Delete an agent and prune workspace/state\n  list          List configured agents\n  set-identity  Update an agent identity (name/theme/emoji/avatar)\n  unbind        Remove routing bindings for an agent\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agents\n\n---\n\nđŠ OpenClaw 2026.4.2 (d74a122) â We ship features faster than Apple ships calculator updates.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent\n---AGENT DIRS---\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/models.json\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/99398699-10a8-4bad-a270-909315f00b8e.jsonl\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json.bak-20260403-230913\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json.bak-20260403-230944\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/a23f7374-28cc-448a-9feb-e9dcc903af11.jsonl.reset.2026-04-03T20-00-37.035Z\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/dat